### EC016-250257 - RFP for Building Condition Report for RCMP Headquarters Divisions (B-H-J-L) 2024-25

#### Tender Details
- **Solicitation Number** : WS4645456102
- **Publication Date** : 2024-07-03
- **Tender Closing Date** : 2024-07-25 14:00:00
- **Amendment Number** : 7
- **Expected Contract Start Date** : 2024-08-27

#### Procurement Category
- **Procurement Method** : Competitive - Selective Tendering
- **Notice Type** : Request for Proposal (RFP) against Supply Arrangement (SA)
- **Procurement Category** : SRV (Services)

#### Request for Proposal (RFP) Description
The Department of Public Works and Government Services (PSPC) is seeking a proposal for a Building Condition Report (BCR) for RCMP Headquarters Divisions (B-H-J-L) for the 2024-2025 fiscal year. The BCR will provide detailed technical and financial information to facilitate timely and prudent development of building management plans and asset management plans.

#### Qualification Requirements
Only firms qualified under the Architectural discipline for the province of Nova Scotia are invited to submit proposals. A list of invited firms is provided below:

1. Arcadis Architects (Canada) Inc. (formerly IBI Group);
2. Acre Architects Inc.;
3. Turner Fleischer Architects Inc.;
4. Root architecture inc.;
5. Fougere Menchenton Architecture Inc.;
6. Trifos Design Consultants Limited;
7. Nadeau Soucy Ellis Architects Inc.;
8. DSRA Architecture Incorporated;
9. EXP Architects Inc.;
10. MacKay-Lyons Sweetapple Architects;
11. Groupe Leclerc Architecture & Design Inc.;
12. SNMArchitect Limited;
13. Stantec Architecture Ltd.;
14. Architecture49 Inc.;
15. Coles Associates Ltd.;
16. Duffus, Romans, Kundzins & Rousefell Limited;
17. EastPoint Architecture Partners;
18. Jarsky Architecture Ltd.;
19. D.F.S. Inc.;
20. Nine Yards Inc.

#### Tender Submissions
Please submit your proposal electronically to the contact person listed below.

#### Contact Information
- **Contact Name** : Carlos Castillo-Nieto
- **Contact Email** : carlos.castillonieto@tpsgc-pwgsc.gc
